Please note that the 2020 census showed high margins of error for the Young CDP.

As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|access-date=January 31, 2008|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref> of 2020, there were 588 people, and 235 households in the CDP.  The population density was {{convert|13.4|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}.  There were 581 housing units at an average density of {{convert|10.06|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}.  The racial makeup of the CDP was 96.08% [[Race (United States Census)|White]], 0.53% [[Race (United States Census)|Native American]], 0.36% [[Race (United States Census)|Asian]], 2.14% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 0.89% from two or more races.  3.39% of the population were [[Race (United States Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Race (United States Census)|Latino]] of any race.

There were 235 households, out of which 8.8% had children under the age of 18 living with them. The  average family size was 2.35.

The median income for a household in the CDP was $40,313, and the median income for a family was $85,673.

